result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Zonte M Wilson

records.descr: DE not competent to stand trial, case suspended

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Zonte M Wilson in court, in custody.  Attorney Melissa Jane Fitzsimmons in court for Zonte M Wilson.  Attorney Dennis Patrick Murphy in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Case in Court for Contested Competency hearing. Discussion placed on the record.  State did not challenge Dr. Collins Report dated 07-15-2022. Defense did challenge Dr. Collins Report dated 07-15-2022. Court qualified Dr. Collins to testify as an expert. Hearing proceeded. 
Sworn for the State:  Dr. Collins.  
Testimony closed. Arguments heard.
After review of all evidence, report of Dr. Collins, and testimony of Dr. Collins, Court found Defendant is NOT COMPETENT TO PROCEED AT THIS TIME, BUT LIKELY TO REGAIN COMPETENCY. Court ordered proceedings suspended. Court ordered Defendant committed to the Department of Health and Family Services for Institutional Care in order to restore competency within the statutory time frame with credit for 62 days time served. Involuntary medication order not ordered at this time. Defendant is REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department for transportation to the designated facility. Court ordered Defendant transported FORTHWITH. Order of Commitment for Treatment (Incompetency), signed and filed. Court ordered case adjourned for Doctor's Report Return. Case remains calendared in Branch 11.
Doctor's Report Return scheduled for December 1, 2022 at 09:00 am.

Attorney Melissa Jane Fitzsimmons in court, defendant Zonte M Wilson not in court, in custody.  Dennis Patrick Murphy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Fitzsimmons informed the court that defendant is challenging Dr. Collins report.  Case adjourned for competency hearing in Branch 25.   All parties are notified that effective July 30, 2022 this case will be assigned to Judge David Swanson, Branch 11, in Room 608 of the Courthouse.  Competency hearing scheduled for August 29, 2022 at 08:30 am.
report of Dr. Collins dated 7/15/2022, received and filed

Defendant Zonte M Wilson in court with attorney Matthew V Plummer.  Defendant Zonte M Wilson in custody.  Alexander James Geocaris appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   All parties appeared by video conference.
  Court is advised by the defense there is reason to believe the defendant is not competent to proceed.  Pursuant to Sec. 971.14 (2) Wisconsin Statutes, Court found probable cause and ordered defendant examined by the Forensic Unit.  Order for Examination, signed and filed.   Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Franke, Branch 25   Court ordered defendant REMANDED into custody of Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.  Doctor's Report Return scheduled for July 18, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
